# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development and fill in your values.
`.env.local` is gitignored and never committed.

```
# Upstash Redis — get these from your Vercel project's Storage tab
# or directly from upstash.com after creating a Redis database
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://your-database-url.upstash.io
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=your-token-here
```

## How to get these values

### On Vercel (production)
1. Open your project in the Vercel dashboard
2. Go to **Integrations** tab → search for **Upstash**
3. Add the Upstash integration and create a Redis database
4. Vercel automatically injects `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL` and
   `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN` into your deployment environment

### Local development
1. Go to [console.upstash.com](https://console.upstash.com)
2. Open your Redis database → **REST API** section
3. Copy the URL and Token into your `.env.local`
